The CD-ROM distribution of the 3.1 Native Developer Kit contains a
number of changes from the original five disk set distribution. The
organization of drawers and disks has been preserved as closely as
possible. Here is the list of changes:

- Unpacked all archive files.

- Moved legal information text to CD-ROM top directory.

- Deleted archive contents listing files

- Added icons to all included files.

- Corrected keyword and function name spellings in the following
  files found in "Docs/doc": datatypes.doc, disk.doc, diskfont.doc,
  dos.doc, exec.doc, expansion.doc, gameport.doc, graphics.doc,
  icon.doc, layers.doc, mathieeedoubbas.doc, mathieeedoubtrans.doc,
  mathieeesingbas.doc, mathieeesingtrans.doc, mathtrans.doc,
  parallel.doc, picture_dtc.doc, printer.doc, serial.doc

- Added smakefiles to all sample programs in "Examples1" and "Examples2".
  All projects can be built using SAS/C 6.56 just by entering "smake".
  All executables were rebuilt using the provided smakefiles to verify
  that the build setup works.

- Updated the contents of "Examples1/AsynchIO". The distribution now
  contains the most recent edition of Martin Taillefer's program code.

- Moved the contents of the drawer "Examples2/DataTypes/datatypes" up
  one level in the filing system hierarchy for ISO 9660 compliance.

- Updated the "Examples2/DataTypes/Src/ClipView" project to
  handle different system gadget sizes properly.

- Moved LHEX program and documentation from "Examples2" into drawer
  of the same name. Replaced LHEX v40.5 with v40.15 which was updated
  by Jim Cooper.

- In "Includes&Libs/linker_libs" amiga.lib v40.15 replaces v40.14. The
  v40.15 release fixes a bug in the memory pool routines. For
  more information see "Includes&Libs/SetPatch40/SetPatch_ReadMe".

- In "Includes&Libs/SetPatch40" SetPatch v40.16 replaces v40.14.
  The v40.16 release fixes a bug in the memory pool routines.

- In "SWToolKit3" the "owner" program was renamed to "memowner" to
  avoid a name clash with the Envoy "Owner" program.

- In "SWToolKit3" CatComp v40.5 replaces v40.4. The v40.5 release
  creates more robust table lookup data and code.

- Removed Enforcer 37.55 from "SWToolKit3"; version 37.64 contributed
  by Mike Sinz replaces this version.
